Task
Create an array of numbers in reverse order, n through 0.
Write a function createReverseArray that takes a non-negative integer n as an argument and returns an array containing integers from n to 0: [n, n-1, ..., 3, 2, 1, 0].
Example:
â€¢ the createReverseArray (5) function must return [5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 0];
â€¢ the createReverseArray (2) function must return [2, 1, 0];
â€¢ the createReverseArray (1) function must return [1, 0];
â€¢ the createReverseArray (0) function must return [0].

Solution
function createReverseArray (n) {
 let arr = [];
  for (let i = n; i> = 0; i -) {
 arr.push (i);
 }
 return arr;
}
